+# Communication-Channel Program Creation Scan
+
+Date: 2026-03-28 (UTC)
+
+## Scope
+Quick static scan for code that either:
+1. Creates/duplicates program entities tied to communication channels, or
+2. Opens/uses communication paths (network/socket/http/event bus), or
+3. Executes external processes that can affect communication behavior.
+
+## Scan commands used
+- `rg -n -i --glob '!README.md' --glob '!*.md' --glob '!*.txt' "\\b(subprocess\\.(run|Popen|call|check_output)|os\\.system\\(|socket\\.socket\\(|requests\\.(get|post|put|delete)|urllib\\.request|http\\.client|smtplib|websocket|WebSocket|slack|twilio|send_mail|email|sms|webhook|channel)\\b"`
+- Follow-up context reads with `nl -ba <file> | sed -n '<start>,<end>p`.
+
+## High-signal findings
+
+### 1) Explicit communication-channel duplication logic
+- `Lancaster/force` duplicates forms when `speaks_on_channel` is set and marks the clone source as `channel-duplicate`. This is direct **program/entity creation tied to communication channels**.
+  - See `_duplicate_channel_speakers` and `source="channel-duplicate"`.
+
+### 2) Event-bus distribution to arbitrary channels
+- `mp3.` defines an `EventBus` and publishes envelopes to every channel in `channels`.
+  - This is explicit **multi-channel communication involvement** and can route generated data to multiple destinations.
+
+### 3) Direct socket communication
+- `AZURE.js` contains socket-based port checks using `socket.socket(...).connect_ex((host, port))`.
+  - This is active network-channel probing.
+
+### 4) HTTP outbound calls
+- `self.system` performs direct `requests.get(url, timeout=...)` for endpoint calls.
+- `SharePoint-PnP` calls external VirusTotal API over HTTP(S) with `requests.get(...)`.
+  - These are external communication channels that could be affected by program logic.
+
+### 5) Process execution that can alter communication controls
+- `AZURE.js` uses `subprocess.run(..., shell=True)` with firewall/service actions (`ufw`, `systemctl`, etc.).
+  - These commands can materially alter inbound/outbound communication paths.
+- `SharePoint-PnP` runs PowerShell commands via `subprocess.run([...])`.
+  - Indirect but high-impact execution surface.
+
+## Risk triage (quick)
+- **High**: Channel duplication / fanout (`Lancaster/force`, `mp3.`) and shell-based firewall manipulation (`AZURE.js`).
+- **Medium**: Direct socket/HTTP usage where targets are runtime-provided (`AZURE.js`, `self.system`, `SharePoint-PnP`).
+- **Medium**: External command execution (`SharePoint-PnP`, `AZURE.js`) due to command-injection and environment-impact potential.
+
+## Recommended next checks
+1. Constrain channel names with allowlists where publish/duplicate is performed.
+2. Replace `shell=True` subprocess usage with argv lists and explicit validation.
+3. Add outbound destination allowlists for HTTP/socket targets.
+4. Add audit logs for all channel fanout and duplication actions.
+5. Add unit tests for deny-by-default behavior on unknown channels.

