+# Communication & Program-Creation Code Scan
+
+Date: 2026-03-28 (UTC)
+Scope scanned: `metadata_reset.py`, `AZURE.js`, and supporting Python/JS files in repo root.
+
+## What was scanned
+- Program/process creation primitives (`exec`, `execSync`, `subprocess.run`, `os.system`, etc.).
+- Communication-channel behavior (HTTP/HTTPS API calls, webhook-like sends, socket usage, remote endpoint posting).
+- Combined risk pattern: code that can both **execute actions** and **communicate externally**.
+
+## Findings
+
+### 1) Direct process execution present
+- `AZURE.js` contains shell command execution via Node `child_process` (`execSync` and `exec`) and command templates that can apply system/cloud changes when not in dry-run mode.
+- `metadata_reset.py` uses `subprocess.run` for Git state-changing operations.
+
+Impact: This enables real operational changes if invoked with execute paths.
+
+### 2) Multiple communication-channel integrations present
+- Frontend/backend-style HTTP calls are present (`fetch('/api/...')` patterns in `AZURE.js`).
+- Outbound API posting is present through Python `requests.post(...)` to Azure Log Analytics ingestion endpoint within `AZURE.js` embedded Python snippets.
+
+Impact: Data can be sent/received across API channels; if combined with execution paths, these are sensitive control points.
+
+### 3) Explicit "execute" API routes are present
+- `AZURE.js` includes several `/execute` route handlers and preview-vs-execute flow examples.
+
+Impact: These routes represent high-value paths where authorization, input validation, and action allowlisting are critical.
+
+## Quick risk judgment
+- **High attention needed** where execute handlers and outbound communication are colocated.
+- The file `AZURE.js` appears to aggregate many mixed snippets and duplicated sections, which increases review and accidental-execution risk.
+
+## Recommended controls
+1. Keep all execute routes defaulting to preview/dry-run unless explicit, strong admin auth + MFA checks pass.
+2. Centralize allowlists for executable commands/actions.
+3. Restrict outbound endpoints to approved host allowlists.
+4. Split monolithic mixed-language files into audited modules to reduce accidental execution.
+5. Add CI static checks for `child_process`, `subprocess`, and `/execute` handler diffs.
+
+## Commands used for the scan
+- `rg --files -g 'AGENTS.md'`
+- `rg --files | head -n 200`
+- `rg -n -i "...communication/network keywords..." ...`
+- `rg -n -i "...execution + communication primitives..." ...`
+- `sed -n '...p' AZURE.js`
+- `sed -n '...p' metadata_reset.py`
